  • Method Details

    • deleteArtifact

      public ArtifactsApi.DeleteArtifactAdapter deleteArtifact(String hrn, String artifactHrn, Optional<Boolean> force)
      Delete the artifact and related files by given HRN. If scoped token is used, then the artifact is deleted within the project the token belongs to. Partial HRN without version could be used. If more than one version of artifact exists and partial HRN is passed then force flag must be set to true. By default force flag is set to false.

      Path: /artifact/{artifactHrn}

      Method: DELETE

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : DeleteArtifactResponse (Successfully deleted existing artifact)

      code 400 : (Invalid artifact details were provided)

      code 401 : (You are not authorized to view the artifact or have wrong / invalid credentials)

      code 403 : (Accessing the artifact is forbidden)

      code 404 : (Specified artifact not found)

      code 500 : ErrorResponse (Internal server error. Support ticket should be created)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      artifactHrn - The HRN of the artifact
      force - The flag to force the deletion even if the artifact is linked to a project

    • listArtifacts

      public ArtifactsApi.ListArtifactsAdapter listArtifacts(Optional<String> access, Optional<String> sort, Optional<String> order, Optional<String> from, Optional<String> groupId, Optional<String> artifactId, Optional<Long> offset, Optional<Integer> limit)
      Return the list of available artifacts. Requires permission to 'apiAccess'.If scoped token is used, then the list of artifacts is returned within the project the token belongs to.If unscoped token is used, then the list of artifacts is returned including the artifacts belonging to the projects.

      Path: /artifact

      Method: GET

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : ListArtifactsResponse (OK)

      code 401 : (You are not authorized to view the artifact or have wrong / invalid credentials)

      code 403 : (Accessing the artifact is forbidden)

      code 400 : (Invalid artifact list parameters were provided)

      code 500 : ErrorResponse (Internal server error. Support ticket should be created)

      Parameters:
      access - Comma separated list of access types (with OR semantic) to filter result.If 'default', returns artifacts user has read access to. If 'orgAdmin', returns artifacts OrgAdmin user has access to.
      sort - Applies sorting based on specified fields. Allowed values are group, name, version. Multiple fields must be separated with ':'
      order - Applies ordering. Defaults is ASC
      from - Applies 'greater than' filtering to fields specified in 'sort' property. For example when 'sort' property is 'name:version' and 'from' is 'b:1.0.0' then the response will contain records with a name starting from 'b' till 'z' and version greater than 1.0.0
      groupId - Applies filtering based on groupId
      artifactId - Applies filtering based on artifactId
      offset - Specifies how many records will be skipped at the beginning. Default is 0
      limit - Specifies the maximum amount of records that could be returned. Default is 20

      public ArtifactsApi.PutArtifactFileAdapter putArtifactFile(String hrn, String artifactHrn, String fileName, byte[] byteArray)
      Upload the file and linked to artifact. Requires permission to 'modifyResource' for the given HRN.

      Path: /artifact/{artifactHrn}/{fileName}

      Method: PUT

      Expected answers:

      code 201 : (The file successfully uploaded)

      code 400 : (Invalid artifact details were provided)

      code 401 : (You are not authorized to view the artifact or have wrong / invalid credentials)

      code 403 : (Accessing the artifact is forbidden)

      code 404 : (Specified artifact not found)

      code 409 : (Request to store a file cannot be completed because there is an ongoing storing operation for the same file.)

      code 500 : ErrorResponse (Internal server error. Support ticket should be created)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      artifactHrn - The HRN of the artifact
      fileName - The name of artifact file
      byteArray -

    • registerArtifact

      public ArtifactsApi.RegisterArtifactAdapter registerArtifact(String groupId, String artifactId, com.here.platform.data.client.base.generated.scaladsl.model.artifact.RegisterArtifactRequest registerArtifactRequest)
      Requires 'accessApi' permission. Create artifact with version 'NONE'. If scoped token is used then the artifact is registered within the project the token belongs to otherwise grant 'readResource', 'modifyResource' and 'shareResource' permissions to app which send request and provided user id

      Path: /artifact/register/{groupId}/{artifactId}

      Method: PUT

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : RegisterArtifactResponse (Artifact already exists)

      code 201 : RegisterArtifactResponse (Successfully created artifact registration record)

      code 400 : (Invalid artifact details were provided)

      code 401 : (You are not authorized to view the artifact or have wrong / invalid credentials)

      code 403 : (Accessing the artifact is forbidden)

      code 500 : ErrorResponse (Internal server error. Support ticket should be created)

      Parameters:
      groupId - The groupId of the artifact. Reversed internet domain name such as com.here.rib.schema
      artifactId - The ID of the artifact
      registerArtifactRequest - The register request which should contains JSON object with userId.
